item.description:
Comprehensions are an elegant way to loop through enumerables, and are especially powerful when the enumerable is heavily nested. Paired with the Collectable protocol they are absolutely fantastic.
Let&rsquo;s walk through doing just that.
@data [ %{ 1 =&gt; [ %{ 1 =&gt; %{ line_items: [ %{ id: 1, to_state: &#34;NJ&#34;, unit_price: 101, quantity: 2 }, %{ id: 1, to_state: &#34;NJ&#34;, unit_price: 50, quantity: 2 } ] } } ] }, %{ 2 =&gt; [ %{ 1 =&gt; %{ line_items: [ %{ id: 1, to_state: &#34;CA&#34;, unit_price: 101, quantity: 2 }, %{ id: 2, to_state: &#34;NJ&#34;, unit_price: 201, quantity: 3 } ] } } ] } ] Here is the data structure we are going to use.
